21. depellere, ‘ drive home,' from pasture. So deducere (uxorem, ete). Gk. κατάγειν.

23. sie, ‘on this principle,' of comparing things by their size. He had imagined Rome to be merely Mantua on a larger scale. whereas he found that it differed in kind as well.
